1
00:00:18,651 --> 00:00:23,089
My Husband is a Mafia Boss is
about unexpected love, power,

2
00:00:23,089 --> 00:00:27,494
dark secrets of the mafia world,
and also finding true love

3
00:00:27,494 --> 00:00:29,496
despite all the differences.

4
00:00:32,198 --> 00:00:36,303
It's a journey of
transformation, redemption,

5
00:00:36,327 --> 00:00:39,246
and the courage to love
in the face of danger.

6
00:00:50,183 --> 00:00:54,892
Of course, there’s more
to come this 2026.

7
00:00:55,187 --> 00:00:58,504
The best-selling novel
by YANALOVESYOUU

8
00:00:58,529 --> 00:01:01,463
My Husband is a Mafia Boss.

9
00:01:04,054 --> 00:01:07,033
Because that has always
been my child’s plan.

10
00:01:07,033 --> 00:01:11,523
That has always
been Yana’s dream.

11
00:01:15,108 --> 00:01:19,682
So many people have read
this novel by Yanalovesyouu.

12
00:01:19,706 --> 00:01:26,448
I think the readers have reached
around 200 million to 300 million globally.

13
00:01:32,234 --> 00:01:34,837
Even though she’s no longer
here, we continue to support

14
00:01:34,837 --> 00:01:40,862
everything she created and
whatever improves her book.

15
00:01:46,840 --> 00:01:51,150
My Husband is a Mafia Boss
is about a girl

16
00:01:51,174 --> 00:01:54,647
who is a bit quirky
and clueless.

17
00:01:54,654 --> 00:01:59,287
Then the man she meets
is serious and stoic.

18
00:01:59,288 --> 00:02:03,523
So what happens when the girl
finds out that the man she loves

19
00:02:03,525 --> 00:02:05,238
is a Mafia Boss?

20
00:02:05,245 --> 00:02:08,492
To read the book, you really
have to go through it cover to cover.

21
00:02:08,498 --> 00:02:10,931
I read it like three times,
it was crazy.

22
00:02:10,931 --> 00:02:12,078
It’s funny.

23
00:02:12,085 --> 00:02:13,738
At the same time,
there’s action.

24
00:02:13,758 --> 00:02:16,436
It will go from laughter
to crying to heartbreak

25
00:02:16,438 --> 00:02:17,915
to devastation and tragedy.

26
00:02:17,922 --> 00:02:20,575
There were times where I
really would laugh in the book.

27
00:02:20,599 --> 00:02:21,834
Even though it’s in Tagalog,
I still get it.

28
00:02:21,834 --> 00:02:24,303
Because I usually prefer English,
it’s obvious.

29
00:02:24,328 --> 00:02:27,180
I laugh because
their dynamic is funny.

30
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:29,625
And I really laugh on my own.

31
00:02:29,650 --> 00:02:32,738
I understand how much
the readers love the book.

32
00:02:32,745 --> 00:02:34,354
I'm a visual person.

33
00:02:34,358 --> 00:02:37,446
I’m not really someone
who reads books a lot.

34
00:02:37,485 --> 00:02:38,562
And I really read the book.

35
00:02:38,586 --> 00:02:41,222
I'm seeing the book
really come to life.

36
00:02:41,222 --> 00:02:44,367
I really fell in love with the story.

37
00:02:44,392 --> 00:02:45,434
Hundred percent.

38
00:02:45,459 --> 00:02:46,459
It’s really true.

39
00:02:46,761 --> 00:02:48,504
I truly loved Aemie.

40
00:02:48,529 --> 00:02:50,407
I truly loved the story.

41
00:02:50,412 --> 00:02:52,748
It’s incredible.
Yanalovesyouu is amazing.

42
00:02:52,773 --> 00:02:54,074
I'm a fan.

43
00:02:54,099 --> 00:02:56,880
I'm very proud that even
though my mom is no longer here,

44
00:02:56,885 --> 00:02:58,121
she still left behind a legacy.

45
00:02:58,145 --> 00:03:00,133
We are here to continue
what she started.

46
00:03:16,257 --> 00:03:20,428
(They’re also acting CEO’s?)

47
00:03:20,731 --> 00:03:22,570
Hello everyone!
Fifth Solomon here.

48
00:03:22,570 --> 00:03:27,175
And I am the director for
the series adaptation of

49
00:03:27,175 --> 00:03:28,975
My Husband is a Mafia Boss.

50
00:03:33,102 --> 00:03:36,605
When Viva One told me
that I would be directing

51
00:03:36,605 --> 00:03:40,387
My Husband is a Mafia Boss,
of course I was very happy because

52
00:03:40,393 --> 00:03:42,623
I really love romantic comedy.

53
00:03:42,632 --> 00:03:46,836
Then it also has a touch of action
that I will be doing for the first time.

54
00:03:46,860 --> 00:03:48,829
So I was really very excited.

55
00:03:48,840 --> 00:03:51,543
At the same time,
of course, there’s pressure.

56
00:03:51,567 --> 00:03:55,560
But when there’s pressure, it’s better
because you prepare even more.

57
00:03:55,584 --> 00:04:01,933
We didn’t expect that her book would
be opened again and turned into a series.

58
00:04:01,957 --> 00:04:06,089
I was really happy because
I saw my mom’s effort.

59
00:04:06,113 --> 00:04:10,967
So it truly deserves
to have an adaptation.

60
00:04:10,991 --> 00:04:12,692
It’s like our third child.

61
00:04:13,727 --> 00:04:15,395
We treat the book like a third child.

62
00:04:15,408 --> 00:04:18,711
Of course, we have our
two grandchildren from Yana.

63
00:04:18,853 --> 00:04:20,588
And then, there’s her book.

64
00:04:20,739 --> 00:04:22,863
We treat it like our own child.

65
00:04:22,888 --> 00:04:26,119
My main vision for
My Husband is a Mafia Boss

66
00:04:26,126 --> 00:04:28,103
is to keep it very light.

67
00:04:28,113 --> 00:04:31,459
Very comedic and romantic.

68
00:04:31,483 --> 00:04:34,670
Even the gunfights and killings.

69
00:04:34,694 --> 00:04:39,188
Very stylized, not morbid
or too bloody.

70
00:04:39,212 --> 00:04:42,282
It still feels light
when you watch it.

71
00:04:42,290 --> 00:04:48,532
But the action scenes
are still cool and stylized.

72
00:04:49,663 --> 00:04:52,666
(How about the lefties?)

73
00:04:57,497 --> 00:04:58,497
What is it, Zeke?

74
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:01,453
I'm leaving for...

75
00:05:02,002 --> 00:05:03,456
I knew it.

76
00:05:04,337 --> 00:05:07,049
How about, “Spotted...”

77
00:05:07,073 --> 00:05:09,795
Excuse me miss, is there
anything I can help you with?

78
00:05:10,315 --> 00:05:11,995
You really never change.

79
00:05:12,845 --> 00:05:14,005
Come on, let’s go over there.

80
00:05:14,180 --> 00:05:16,649
Is this really the right use
of my good looks?

81
00:05:16,875 --> 00:05:19,200
I have something I want
to confess to you, Moo.

82
00:05:19,411 --> 00:05:20,574
I gathered my courage.

83
00:05:20,686 --> 00:05:23,956
Confessed—and now,
I have a girlfriend. See?

84
00:05:24,142 --> 00:05:26,141
Just say yes to me. Please.

85
00:05:27,026 --> 00:05:28,381
You look so tired.

86
00:05:28,694 --> 00:05:29,821
Let’s go inside?

87
00:05:29,962 --> 00:05:31,697
Hey, why so quiet?

88
00:05:31,697 --> 00:05:33,243
Oh come on, tell me something.

89
00:05:33,566 --> 00:05:34,910
Stop pouting like that.

90
00:05:34,934 --> 00:05:36,444
It’s annoying to look at.

91
00:05:37,003 --> 00:05:40,516
We held auditions for
My Husband is a Mafia Boss.

92
00:05:40,530 --> 00:05:44,584
And of course, it was
very challenging to choose

93
00:05:44,598 --> 00:05:49,583
which actors
would fit the roles.

94
00:05:49,590 --> 00:05:53,436
Especially since there are so
many characters in this novel.

95
00:05:53,443 --> 00:05:57,142
So we really examined
who would fit.

96
00:05:57,148 --> 00:06:00,294
Physically, and their
character as well.

97
00:06:00,308 --> 00:06:06,466
Because for me, I believe that
90 percent of directing is casting

98
00:06:06,477 --> 00:06:08,035
the right people.

99
00:06:18,879 --> 00:06:20,317
Hi, I'm Aaliyah Coco.

100
00:06:20,324 --> 00:06:21,545
Hi, I'm Dann Aquino.

101
00:06:21,550 --> 00:06:23,265
Hi, I am Icee Ejercito.

102
00:06:23,277 --> 00:06:25,324
Hello guys, it's Kyosu Guinto.

103
00:06:25,349 --> 00:06:27,594
Hello everyone,
it's Jaime Yllana.

104
00:06:27,619 --> 00:06:28,858
And I play the role of...

105
00:06:28,871 --> 00:06:30,423
Nico Jeisz Young.

106
00:06:30,438 --> 00:06:31,438
Louie Birkins.

107
00:06:31,451 --> 00:06:32,451
Caileigh Ferrer.

108
00:06:32,476 --> 00:06:33,853
Shan Venice Birkins.

109
00:06:33,881 --> 00:06:35,200
Kevin Alferez.

110
00:06:36,512 --> 00:06:38,781
What happened during
the audition was...

111
00:06:38,806 --> 00:06:40,592
First, I was asked
to read for Kevin.

112
00:06:40,617 --> 00:06:44,106
They said I was okay for
Kevin based on the script I read.

113
00:06:44,378 --> 00:06:46,760
Then for Louie as well,
it was also okay.

114
00:06:47,281 --> 00:06:49,917
So I ended up being
considered for both roles.

115
00:06:49,917 --> 00:06:54,588
In the end, I got Kevin Alferez
in the audition.

116
00:06:56,791 --> 00:06:59,358
I was asked to
read different roles.

117
00:06:59,819 --> 00:07:01,778
Not really Nico.

118
00:07:02,329 --> 00:07:03,597
Yeah, I know.

119
00:07:03,622 --> 00:07:05,036
I wasn’t really meant for Nico.

120
00:07:05,061 --> 00:07:08,008
But when I went in,
Direk Fifth said,

121
00:07:08,808 --> 00:07:10,040
why don’t you try this.

122
00:07:10,743 --> 00:07:12,086
And they liked it.

123
00:07:12,100 --> 00:07:16,316
But I thought I wouldn’t get it
because I was very nervous.

124
00:07:16,323 --> 00:07:20,233
But they trusted me to
get Nico Jeisz Young.

125
00:07:20,703 --> 00:07:23,181
I worked hard for
this to show all of you.

126
00:07:25,948 --> 00:07:29,249
I remember I was feeling
super nervous that day

127
00:07:29,253 --> 00:07:31,846
because there were
so many people at Viva.

128
00:07:31,860 --> 00:07:34,843
And I didn’t really know
what to expect.

129
00:07:34,868 --> 00:07:37,381
Actually at that time,
I hadn’t read the book yet.

130
00:07:37,625 --> 00:07:40,677
So I was just getting to
know the characters based on

131
00:07:40,684 --> 00:07:43,329
one short scene.

132
00:07:43,675 --> 00:07:47,987
And honestly, I connected more
to Venice because she’s edgier.

133
00:07:48,231 --> 00:07:50,896
But I auditioned
for Caileigh first.

134
00:07:50,896 --> 00:07:53,899
So my audition for
Caileigh was a bit shaky.

135
00:07:53,924 --> 00:07:58,906
And then my audition
for Venice was smoother.

136
00:07:58,920 --> 00:08:02,048
So I was shocked when
I found out that I got Caileigh.

137
00:08:04,247 --> 00:08:07,996
When I went to the place,
they gave us scripts

138
00:08:08,003 --> 00:08:11,349
on the spot, and I had
to read lines and practice.

139
00:08:11,363 --> 00:08:14,129
And for me, that part
was pretty exciting.

140
00:08:14,136 --> 00:08:17,666
I was excited to
explore a new character.

141
00:08:17,676 --> 00:08:22,403
And luckily, Shan Venice Birkins
is someone I can relate to

142
00:08:22,411 --> 00:08:26,415
in terms of her personality,
the way she is, her nuances.

143
00:08:26,439 --> 00:08:28,957
And when I got into the
room for the actual audition,

144
00:08:28,981 --> 00:08:32,741
I think it was crazy that
I had no nerves at all.

145
00:08:32,766 --> 00:08:34,247
Maybe God was really with me.

146
00:08:34,272 --> 00:08:36,514
God walked into that
room with me that day.

147
00:08:36,538 --> 00:08:38,665
I didn’t feel nervous at all.

148
00:08:38,690 --> 00:08:40,692
And I did my best.

149
00:08:40,881 --> 00:08:47,083
And I also remember I auditioned
for Fiona, as well as Caileigh.

150
00:08:47,280 --> 00:08:51,068
But yeah, Shan Venice was home,
so I ended up here.

151
00:08:54,854 --> 00:08:57,546
I auditioned for the role of
Sebastian and Louie Birkins.

152
00:08:57,570 --> 00:08:59,705
But maybe Sebastian
is just too handsome.

153
00:09:00,339 --> 00:09:00,940
I’m just cute.

154
00:09:00,940 --> 00:09:03,842
Actually, they told me
I should only pick one.

155
00:09:03,867 --> 00:09:06,612
But I asked if I could
try Louie Birkins.

156
00:09:06,624 --> 00:09:08,040
Because I felt like
that was really me.

157
00:09:08,064 --> 00:09:10,116
So now, here I am.

158
00:09:11,404 --> 00:09:15,875
The first character that I was
auditioning for was the role

159
00:09:15,875 --> 00:09:17,323
that I got, Amesyl Cross.

160
00:09:17,669 --> 00:09:20,249
At first, I was so worried.

161
00:09:20,280 --> 00:09:22,983
I really wasn't sure
of my performance.

162
00:09:22,983 --> 00:09:26,987
Because Amesyl truly is so
different from the characters that

163
00:09:26,987 --> 00:09:28,328
I'm used to playing.

164
00:09:28,608 --> 00:09:31,702
So Amesyl’s approach is different.

165
00:09:31,727 --> 00:09:36,270
And I was worried that maybe
I wouldn’t be able to pull it off.

166
00:09:36,589 --> 00:09:41,495
But fortunately, thankfully,
I got the role that I auditioned for.

167
00:09:41,968 --> 00:09:43,937
And that’s it.

168
00:09:44,571 --> 00:09:48,926
When I first found out,
my best friend also got the role of Kaizer.

169
00:09:48,950 --> 00:09:50,919
And on the phone, we were
congratulating each other.

170
00:09:50,944 --> 00:09:53,380
And I was like,
congrats, we got it.

171
00:09:53,380 --> 00:09:55,982
Because even during
the audition, we were like,

172
00:09:55,982 --> 00:09:57,250
you're auditioning for Kaizer?

173
00:09:57,275 --> 00:09:58,815
I'm auditioning for Amesyl.

174
00:09:58,839 --> 00:10:00,119
You know they’re endgame, right?

175
00:10:08,728 --> 00:10:10,829
Hello everyone,
I’m Maru Delgado.

176
00:10:10,854 --> 00:10:12,655
Hello everyone, I’m PJ Rosario.

177
00:10:12,679 --> 00:10:14,614
Hello everyone, I’m Alamat R-Ji.

178
00:10:14,627 --> 00:10:16,292
Hey everybody,
this is Frost Sandoval.

179
00:10:16,316 --> 00:10:17,884
I'm gonna portray
the role of...

180
00:10:17,889 --> 00:10:18,889
Jacob Lee.

181
00:10:18,896 --> 00:10:19,896
Sebastian Lerwick.

182
00:10:19,909 --> 00:10:20,993
Vash Boulstridge.

183
00:10:21,018 --> 00:10:22,419
Kaizer Maxwell Lamperouge.

184
00:10:22,443 --> 00:10:23,625
Do you see that?

185
00:10:23,632 --> 00:10:27,069
There were so many of us when
we were called to audition for the role

186
00:10:27,093 --> 00:10:30,403
and if I’m not mistaken,
I tried about four roles.

187
00:10:30,446 --> 00:10:32,888
I’m happy and
grateful that finally,

188
00:10:32,901 --> 00:10:36,026
I was given the role
of Vash Boulstridge.

189
00:10:36,057 --> 00:10:40,391
If I’m not mistaken,
I auditioned for Jacob.

190
00:10:40,608 --> 00:10:42,918
I auditioned for Kaizer.

191
00:10:42,943 --> 00:10:46,322
When I got Vash,
I was so happy, so happy.

192
00:10:46,346 --> 00:10:51,351
And I’m very excited
because aside from the Vash

193
00:10:51,356 --> 00:10:57,389
that people know from the book,
maybe I can bring something

194
00:10:57,403 --> 00:10:58,629
unique as well.

195
00:11:00,775 --> 00:11:03,618
I felt like at that time,
I wouldn’t make it.

196
00:11:03,643 --> 00:11:06,599
Because knowing how
many people auditioned,

197
00:11:06,624 --> 00:11:09,449
every time I audition,
I never expect to get the role.

198
00:11:09,830 --> 00:11:13,183
I just pray that I can
be part of the project,

199
00:11:13,197 --> 00:11:14,903
because there’s
no big or small role.

200
00:11:15,509 --> 00:11:16,816
See you guys later.

201
00:11:17,177 --> 00:11:21,480
We were called to audition
for My Husband is a Mafia Boss.

202
00:11:21,505 --> 00:11:24,184
So to be honest, I really had
no idea what was going on.

203
00:11:24,208 --> 00:11:26,727
Like, what is this?
What’s happening?

204
00:11:27,017 --> 00:11:30,751
They had us audition,
gave us a script, and suddenly,

205
00:11:30,776 --> 00:11:32,202
Okay, you’re next.

206
00:11:32,208 --> 00:11:34,460
I think they gave
me about two pages.

207
00:11:34,695 --> 00:11:37,821
So I really got nervous,
I was really nervous, but I did my best.

208
00:11:37,846 --> 00:11:41,250
In my mind, I really
had to be in character as

209
00:11:41,275 --> 00:11:44,092
Jacob Lee,
like I had to embody him.

210
00:11:44,116 --> 00:11:47,808
I meditated, I really thought about

211
00:11:47,808 --> 00:11:49,143
what the character is,

212
00:11:49,143 --> 00:11:51,078
what kind of personality he has.

213
00:11:53,581 --> 00:11:57,083
And when I got there,
I told myself,

214
00:11:57,344 --> 00:11:58,504
I hope I’m not the first one.

215
00:11:58,912 --> 00:11:59,916
Right?

216
00:11:59,941 --> 00:12:01,709
I wasn’t first, I was second.

217
00:12:01,721 --> 00:12:04,728
So I was still able
to review my lines.

218
00:12:04,748 --> 00:12:06,640
We were running
lines with Sarah.

219
00:12:06,664 --> 00:12:11,816
I was auditioning for the
role of Kaizer and Nico Jeisz.

220
00:12:11,842 --> 00:12:13,566
But I was extremely nervous.

221
00:12:13,731 --> 00:12:16,096
Of course, you can
only do this once.

222
00:12:16,120 --> 00:12:19,460
So I could say that I
did the best that I could,

223
00:12:19,485 --> 00:12:23,558
given the time and the
circumstance that I was in.

224
00:12:25,807 --> 00:12:26,840
Hi guys!

225
00:12:26,865 --> 00:12:31,068
I’m Rhen Escaño, and I am
your Aemie Romero-Roswell.

226
00:12:36,347 --> 00:12:39,692
Aemie is an ordinary
girl studying at

227
00:12:39,717 --> 00:12:41,388
Stonehurst University.

228
00:12:41,412 --> 00:12:46,150
She is the heart of the story,
and she’s the ray of sunshine.

229
00:12:46,190 --> 00:12:48,760
Her life is very, very colorful.

230
00:12:48,785 --> 00:12:51,871
The world she lives
in is very colorful.

231
00:12:51,895 --> 00:12:55,279
She’s the one who always
brings happiness to people.

232
00:12:55,303 --> 00:12:56,533
Slowpoke!

233
00:12:56,564 --> 00:12:59,765
But she’s really smart,
academically.

234
00:12:59,790 --> 00:13:00,794
She’s really smart.

235
00:13:00,819 --> 00:13:04,360
And in the story,
we also discover that Aemie

236
00:13:04,384 --> 00:13:05,717
knows how to love.

237
00:13:10,648 --> 00:13:14,185
When I was in high school,
we had so many similarities.

238
00:13:14,185 --> 00:13:17,588
The way she gives
positive energy

239
00:13:17,588 --> 00:13:20,445
and good vibes to
the people around her.

240
00:13:20,470 --> 00:13:25,013
Being playful,
being the life of the party.

241
00:13:25,038 --> 00:13:28,609
That’s how I was in high school,
I always wanted

242
00:13:28,634 --> 00:13:30,098
the people around
me to be happy,

243
00:13:30,122 --> 00:13:32,111
especially my friends and my family.

244
00:13:32,117 --> 00:13:35,991
The energy I give them
is very important to me.

245
00:13:36,015 --> 00:13:38,551
